CAPE TOWN - President Jacob Zuma will be meeting with Elsies River residents at a crime-fighting imbizo on Tuesday. The Cape Flats community is still reeling after the rape and murder of three-year-old Courtney Pieters.President Zuma visited Pieters family earlier this month.READ: Elsies River: A community under siegeAn alleged close friend of Pieters' parents and a boarder in their home has been charged with her murder.Zuma has pledged more support to the victims of crime, specifically children.He also said police must improve their services in the area.Zuma has called on citizens to unite against the brutal killing of women and children.eNCA